    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-15T12:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-15T12:36:00-05:00" n="212"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/24209: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-15T11:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1920—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>288. It is reported that the diplomatic corps will soon be invited to meet
                    Provisional President de la Huerta. The dean of the diplomatic corps, in the
                    belief that the Provisional Government is legally constituted and that
                    recognition is unnecessary, states that he is disposed to accept such an
                    invitation when extended.</p>
                <pb facs="0272" n="172" xml:id="pg_172"/>
                <p>One of the local papers today prints a statement evidently given out by the
                    Foreign Office to the effect that the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of France has
                    announced that it regards the Provisional Government of Mexico as [legally]
                    constituted and that special recognition is therefore unnecessary.</p>
                <p>Mr. Iglesias Calderón intimated to me yesterday that he felt he would be able to
                    make clear in Washington that the present Provisional Government in Mexico is
                    the legal Constitutional successor of the Carranza Government and that
                    rerecognition is unnecessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
